content: Woman, 38, died at the scene Truck driver was not injured A woman has died after her car collided with a livestock truck on a busy highway.
The car and the truck crashed on the Princes Highway near the coastal town of Port Fairy, in Victorian, at 6pm on Wednesday.The 38-year-old driver of the car died at the scene.

The truck driver escaped injury and is currently assisting police with their inquiries. The truck was not carrying any livestock at the time of the crash.The highway was closed near Dura Lane after the crash to allow Major Collision Investigation Unit detectives to investigate at the scene.Anyone who witnessed the crash or who may have dashcam video is asked to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000 or at www.crimestoppersvic.com.au.
